Description: Bluetooth A2DP sink with DSP EQ and web UI
 SoundSync turns a headless Linux box into a Bluetooth A2DP audio sink
 with a DSP equaliser and a browser-accessible control interface.
 .
 The daemon runs as a systemd user service inside the PipeWire session.
 A root oneshot service sets the Bluetooth adapter Class-of-Device and
 HCI name at boot (requires CAP_NET_ADMIN via hciconfig).
